To create a plan to make you a sandwich, I'll outline the steps below.

<plan>
{
  "name": "Make Sandwich",
  "type": "sequence",
  "children": [
    {
      "name": "Gather Ingredients",
      "type": "fallback",
      "children": [
        {
          "name": "Check if Bread is Available",
          "type": "action",
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Bread",
          "type": "retry",
          "children": [
            {
              "name": "Attempt to Get Bread",
              "type": "action",
              "children": []
            }
          ],
          "attempts": 3
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Assemble Sandwich",
      "type": "sequence",
      "children": [
        {
          "name": "Slice Bread",
          "type": "action",
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Add Filling",
          "type": "action",
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Assemble Sandwich",
          "type": "fallback",
          "children": [
            {
              "name": "Check if Filling is Applied",
              "type": "action",
              "children": []
            },
            {
              "name": "Apply More Filling",
              "type": "retry",
              "children": [
                {
                  "name": "Attempt to Apply More Filling",
                  "type": "action",
                  "children": []
                }
              ],
              "attempts": 2
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Cut Sandwich",
          "type": "action",
          "children": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Serve and Enjoy",
      "type": "action",
      "children": []
    }
  ]
}
</plan>

This plan outlines the steps to gather ingredients, assemble the sandwich, and finally serve and enjoy. It includes fallbacks and retries to ensure that the necessary actions are taken in case of any issues during the process.
